(ix) the increased asset base.

(i) unlocking the value of the Demerged Undertaking for the shareholders of the demerged company;
(ii) attracting investors and providing better flexibility in accessing capital;
(iii) segregating different businesses having different risk and return profiles, and providing investors with better flexibility to select investment which best suit their investment strategies and risk profile;
(iv) effective utilisation of cash flows of different business and limiting restrictions arising out of different terms of different lenders for different businesses;
(v) enabling focused growth strategy for each of the businesses for exploiting opportunities specific to each business;
